=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">What=E2=80=99s <strong>Drake</strong> goin=
g to do about the Super Bowl?
The Canadian rapper just launched a blockbuster defamation lawsuit against =
Universal Music Group for releasing and promoting <strong>Kendrick Lamar</s=
trong>=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9CNot Like Us,=E2=80=9D a diss track that disparage=
s Drake as, among other things, a =E2=80=9Ccertified pedophile.=E2=80=9D In=
 less than three weeks, Lamar is slated to headline the Super Bowl halftime=
 show, where he=E2=80=99s expected to perform =E2=80=9CNot Like Us=E2=80=9D=
 in front of 65,000 fans in New Orleans and <em>100 million-plus</em> watch=
ing on TV. Could Drake attempt to push
the NFL and Fox to prevent Lamar from performing the song?=C2=A0=C2=A0</p><=
p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;marg=
in-bottom:0px;">That=E2=80=99s hard to say. Theoretically, repeating someth=
ing false qualifies as a <em>republication</em>, and if the NFL, Fox, or th=
e halftime show=E2=80=99s producer, <strong>Jay Z</strong>=E2=80=99s Roc Na=
tion, gave Lamar the microphone to tell new audiences about Drake=E2=80=99s=
 supposed sins, they could be as potentially liable as UMG. (Especially now=
 that Drake
has made everyone aware of the falsity of the statements, if they are indee=
d false.) However, Drake=E2=80=99s endgame here is=E2=80=A6 murky. It=E2=80=
=99s unlikely he=E2=80=99s after a payout=E2=80=94he=E2=80=99s already load=
ed, and the lawsuit only amplifies Lamar=E2=80=99s insult. Meanwhile, both =
Drake <em>and</em> Lamar have record deals with UMG units: Lamar with Inter=
scope, Drake with Republic. Some speculate that Drake might be aiming to wi=
ggle out of his record deal, although this would be a strange way to do it.=
 Quite a few lawyers
have emphasized to me that Drake=E2=80=99s lawsuit is targeting only Lamar=
=E2=80=99s <em>label</em>, not Lamar directly. The decision to not go after=
 the speaker most responsible for the trash talk seems=E2=80=A6 calculated.=
=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"ma=
rgin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Yet, the theory that Drake is merely out to esca=
pe his UMG contract stumbles a bit. According to his 81-page complaint, his=
 deal is nearly up. In fact, rather wildly, Drake alleges that UMG ignored =
his
objections and hyper-marketed =E2=80=9CNot Like Us=E2=80=9D because the com=
pany wanted to devalue his brand and music in order to gain leverage in ext=
ension talks=E2=80=94while simultaneously courting favor with Lamar, whose =
own contract was also ending. Does that make any sense? No matter. Drake go=
es even further, claiming that Lamar wrote and recorded =E2=80=9CNot Like U=
s=E2=80=9D as part of a strategy by Interscope C.E.O. <strong>John Janick</=
strong> to position himself over Republic=E2=80=99s <strong>Monte Lipman
</strong>as the successor to UMG C.E.O. <strong>Lucian Grainge</strong>. (S=
eriously, <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1=
lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVaTlwYXNnODV2bGptcVFSbWh6QT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZ=
G9jdW1lbnRjbG91ZC5vcmcvZG9jdW1lbnRzLzI1NDk5Mzg5LWRyYWtlLWNvbXBsYWludC8_dXRt=
X2NhbXBhaWduPVdoYXQrSSUyN20rSGVhcmluZyUyQistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyMSU=
yRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSU=
JFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyN=
nV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEi=
LCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwNTE4ODB9/2740a8=
38ba1bb84e668e217ea88cde9d1a2ecda6943a06a6626840cc425ad837" style=3D"text-d=
ecoration:underline;color:#d40000;">read it for yourself</a>.)</p><p style=
=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">So what=
=E2=80=99s really driving Drake? Maybe it=E2=80=99s just plain sensitivity.=
 More and more, public figures are turning to the courts to clean up reputa=
tional messes=E2=80=94a strategy that often proves
questionable. In any case, the NFL and Fox should brace themselves. Drake=
=E2=80=99s reps previously denied sending a cease-and-desist letter over La=
mar=E2=80=99s Super Bowl gig, but that was <em>before</em> Drake filed this=
 suit.=C2=A0</p></div>
