jgxJTJGMTQlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Nv=
dXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGV=
ybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA1MTg4MX0/70c5e459a30468=
14ccacaf9b11ce923b086f00765351c5905445764391480ca6" style=3D"text-decoratio=
n:underline;color:#d40000;">179-page complaint</a>, orchestrated by <strong=
>Bryan Freedman</strong>, could give <strong>Tolstoy</strong> a run for his=
 money with its intricate narrative of allegiances and betrayals, targeting=
 not just Lively, but also her husband, <strong>Ryan Reynolds</strong>, and=
 publicist <strong>Leslie Sloane</strong>. The tome frames the dispute not =
as mere celebrity
squabbling, but as =E2=80=9Ctwo of the most powerful stars in the world dep=
loying their enormous power to steal an entire film right out of the hands =
of its director and production studio.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">L=
ooking ahead, keep an eye on how each side tries to probe the other=E2=80=
=99s vulnerabilities for leverage. Consider the claim that Lively and Reyno=
lds meddled with Baldoni=E2=80=99s relationship with WME: This could lead t=
o interesting
revelations during discovery, given the talent agency=E2=80=99s conflicting=
 alliances and penchant for oral arrangements with its star clients.=C2=A0<=
/p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;=
margin-bottom:0px;">There=E2=80=99s also the subplot involving <strong>Tayl=
or Swift</strong>, one of Lively=E2=80=99s best friends, who has been pulle=
d into the fray for allegedly pressuring Baldoni to include script rewrites=
 by Lively. You can bet that cameo will whet the appetite of the press, as
will the accusation that Reynolds lampooned Baldoni in <em>Deadpool &amp; W=
olverine=E2=80=94</em>although I have trouble figuring out what=E2=80=99s l=
egally problematic about poking fun at a guy=E2=80=99s self-identification =
as a feminist. (Perhaps Freedman will argue it violated a non-disparagement=
 agreement, but I=E2=80=99m <em>highly</em> dubious that Reynolds, who wasn=
=E2=80=99t even party to a deal over the the promotion of <em>It Ends With =
Us,</em> can=E2=80=99t draw inspiration for a <em>fictional</em> character =
in another movie.)=C2=A0
And surely, Disney and Sony would prefer to steer clear of the drama. Freed=
man=E2=80=99s latest strategic move=E2=80=94submitting <em>It Ends With Us<=
/em> <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt=
2UktxclJLZ0dVaTlwYXNnODV2bGptcVFSbWh6QT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cudG16Lm=
NvbS8yMDI1LzAxLzIxL2p1c3Rpbi1iYWxkb25pLWl0LWVuZHMtd2l0aC11cy1yYXctZm9vdGFnZ=
S1kYW5jZS1zY2VuZS1uby1zZXh1YWwtaGFyYXNzbWVudC1ibGFrZS1saXZlbHkvP3V0bV9jYW1w=
YWlnbj1XaGF0K0klMjdtK0hlYXJpbmclMkIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJTJGMjElMkYyNSU=
yOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVdoYXQrSSUyN20rSGVhcmluZyUyQistK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKy=
UyODElMkYxNCUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG1fc=
291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwiaW50=
ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDUxODgyfQ/cb8833d553df=
3aa390d45bcd44497470823963ff6a805564188d67b902bab93d" style=3D"text-decorat=
ion:underline;color:#d40000;">outtakes</a> to the Central District of TMZ=
=E2=80=94is bound to raise eyebrows and hints at stratagems to come. (Remem=
ber, Baldoni has also filed a $250 million defamation suit against
<em>The New York Times</em> for its =E2=80=9CWe Can Bury Anyone=E2=80=9D <a=
 href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktxcl=
JLZ0dVaTlwYXNnODV2bGptcVFSbWh6QT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb=
20vMjAyNC8xMi8yMS9idXNpbmVzcy9tZWRpYS9ibGFrZS1saXZlbHktanVzdGluLWJhbGRvbmkt=
aXQtZW5kcy13aXRoLXVzLmh0bWw_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVdoYXQrSSUyN20rSGVhcmluZyUyQis=
tK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyMSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9V2hhdCtJJT=
I3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjE0JTJGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fb=
WVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3VzdG9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1f=
dGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSI=
sImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwMjU4NjV9/4a02202722b98c605a7fbafa3dffaf282af84038797e9120b=
8042fc8c787cf65" style=3D"text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">story</=
a>, published just before Christmas.)</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom=
:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Meanwhile, Baldon=
i, who was unceremoniously dropped by WME in December, might appear to have=
 little left to lose from a protracted
fight. But not so for his co-plaintiff <strong>Melissa Nathan</strong>, who=
se high-octane P.R. shop juggles clients including <strong>Johnny Depp</str=
ong>, <strong>Logan Paul</strong>, and=E2=80=A6 Drake. I=E2=80=99m frankly =
surprised she agreed to be a co-plaintiff in this case, which may subject h=
er high-profile clientele to unwanted exposure.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin=
:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;">This legal saga may=
 stretch on for <em>years</em>=E2=80=94especially with so many players of a=
ll
kinds on the stage. Also, don=E2=80=99t overlook the lawsuit against Baldon=
i, launched by publicist <strong>Stephanie Jones</strong>, who once represe=
nted the filmmaker and then cooperated with Lively=E2=80=99s team when he d=
ropped her for Nathan. This is really a <em>three</em>-way battle.=C2=A0</p=
></div>
