DEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA1MTg4M30/=
b5c72246f3be50c040f33a39eaadea0d68d893374e24622ee18136bd149147c5" style=3D"=
text-decoration:underline;color:#d40000;">decision</a> in <em>Philip Morris=
 USA v. Williams</em>, where a $79.5 million punitive damages verdict was o=
verturned as an unconstitutional violation of due process, since
it was based on a jury=E2=80=99s desire to punish the defendant for health =
damages suffered by cigarette smokers who weren=E2=80=99t involved in the c=
ase. Similarly, CNN argued that punitive damages shouldn=E2=80=99t be a veh=
icle for punishing CNN for the sins of the broader media industry, a nuance=
d point that the judge was urged to consider. If the parties had not settle=
d, Judge Henry=E2=80=99s interpretation=E2=80=94that while the jury=E2=80=
=99s punitive damages shouldn=E2=80=99t reflect a general punishment for wh=
at the media had done
historically, the damages could still act as a deterrent against future jou=
rnalistic slipperiness=E2=80=94might have ripened into a potent appellate i=
ssue</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Further complicating matters, Judge Henry was nudg=
ed toward the <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVD=
J4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVaTlwYXNnODV2bGptcVFSbWh6QT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9zd=
XByZW1lLmp1c3RpYS5jb20vY2FzZXMvZmVkZXJhbC91cy81MzgvNDA4Lz91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249=
V2hhdCtJJTI3bStIZWFyaW5nJTJCKy0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjIxJTJGMjUlMjlcdTA=
wMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1XaGF0K0klMjdtK0hlYXJpbmclMkIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJT=
JGMTQlMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZ=
T1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFs=
IjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MzkyMDk4fQ/d506f8688eadc0c46f65=
1c5869d4480977e4d6ad608c8c1579ab8190f594c039" style=3D"text-decoration:unde=
rline;color:#d40000;"><em>State Farm v. Campbell</em></a> precedent, sugges=
ting punitive damages
shouldn=E2=80=99t dwarf compensatory ones by more than a single-digit multi=
plier. For all the saber-rattling from the right, framing this as a billion=
-dollar showdown, and despite Young=E2=80=99s team salivating at the prospe=
ct of a $150 million punitive windfall, the initial $5 million compensatory=
 verdict actually offered CNN a lifeline, potentially capping its total exp=
osure at $50 million=E2=80=94a bitter pill, no doubt, but far from a ruinou=
s blow.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;">I bet the settlement hovered around half that=E2=80=94say, $25 mi=
llion=E2=80=94to sidestep the hazards of an appeal. Some media advocates mi=
ght balk at the figure, deeming it steep, yet considering the appellate ben=
ch is peppered with appointees from <strong>Ron DeSantis</strong> and Trump=
, it=E2=80=99s hardly far-fetched. For CNN, it=E2=80=99s a <strong>Jake Tap=
per</strong>-sized gulp, the price of shaking off a persistent headache. La=
te to the game, sure, but as the old adage goes: Better late than never,
especially when the lesson is this costly.</p></div>
